========================================

Playtesting Requirements
========================================
[ ] - Your handin meets all Nin1 primary requirements.
[ ] - The player must be able to fire projectiles.
(Beam to shoot down bullets)


Primary Engine Requirements
========================================

[ ] - Your engine must correctly implement saving and loading through serialization.
(Yes)
[ ] - Your engine must correctly support raycasting for polygons and AABs.
(Yes. Doesn't support raycasting for circles)

Primary Game Requirements
========================================
[ ] - Your game must load from a txt file.
(Use CSV file. File can be located in resources folder)

[ ] - You must have at least one txt file for us to load (unless your game loads from our default level file)
(Game loads with high score)

[ ] - Player must be able to
	[ ] - save game state

		(Current coin and lives count is stored. Highscore is saved if it has changed)

	[ ] - restart the game

		(Press end game or lose all your lives)

	[ ] - load their saved state

		(load saved state will load the saved coin and lives count)

[ ] - The player must always be in view
	(Player is not able to jump off screen)

[ ] - The TA debugger must be completed to demonstrate correct raycasting for polygons and AABs.
	(Went into detail of what happens in the INSTRUCTIONS. I works)

[ ] - It must be possible to start a new game without restarting the program

	(You can lose all your lives or you can press end game. If you press end game, you will be taken to the main game screen. You have to navigate back to the game NIN)


Secondary Engine Requirements (N/A)
=======================================
[ ] - Handin meets all primary engine requirements
[ ] - Your engine must support raycasting for circles

Secondary Game Requirements (N/A)
======================================
[ ] - Handin meets all primary game requirements
[ ] - The TA debugger must be completed to demonstrate correct raycasting for circles.
[ ] - Raycasting must be implemented in your game as follows:
	[ ] - player can fire bullets which travel instantly
	[ ] - bullets must apply an impulse to whatever they hit in the direction of the ray
[ ] - Your game meets at least two of the Nin extra requirements (please list which ones you chose!)




[ ] - Handin isn't permanent fixed size
(I limited the size of the screen to pass this checkpoint)


